newsitem.title: USA: Nasdaq ends Friday session, week with losses.
newsitem.headline: Nasdaq ends Friday session, week with losses.

text.p: Nasdaq stocks lost power in Friday's final trading hour to finish with a loss after trading near unchanged for most of the session.
The Nasdaq composite index fell 4.4 points, or 0.36 percent, to close unoffically at 1222.6 and close the week with a loss of almost 20 points.
Declining issues outnumbered gainers by 21 to 19, while the day yielded 128 new highs and 108 new lows on unofficial volume of 565 million shares.
The Nasdaq 100 also fell from a slight gain to a loss in the final hours of trade, ending at 743.6, off 4.8 points.
The Nasdaq's most active issue was also one of the biggest loser: Octel Communications Corp tumbled 8-3/4 to 15-3/4 after its quarterly results failed to meet Wall Street expectations.
Conversely, American Power Conversion Corp ended 1-7/8 higher at 18-1/8, 1/8 below an all-time high reached during the day, after reporting stronger-than-forecast third quarter results.
Also, Intel shed 2-1/8 to 105-3/8 and Microsoft slipped 3/16 to 136-7/16.
